              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Intrinsic coordinate ranges from 0 (at port 0) to 1 (at port 1), unitless. Reference is the nominal geometry of the linear element that must be available to define the intermediate values. Linear referencing method is interpolating.

Intrinsic positions can also be defined as full linear positions, using full ISO 19148. The representation provided here is a shorthand for direct use by the topology ontology.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
